HEADWORD: Patronomatology
<hw>Pa`tro*nom`a*tol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>path`r</grk>, <grk>patro`s</grk>, a father + E.
<ets>onomatology</ets>.]</ety> <def>That branch of knowledge which deals
with personal names and their origin; the study of
patronymics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

